Looking for a super quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Super Quick Spaghetti Beef Ragu in just 15 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

== Beef Ragu ==

Boil a full #kettle{}.

While it boils, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%grams}, about ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break up the mince as it cooks. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Spaghetti{180%grams}, about ~{8%minutes}.

Once the beef has browned, drain the fat.

Stir in the @Mixed Herbs{1%sachet} and @Worcester Sauce{15%grams}. Simmer, about ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{25%grams}, @Red Wine Jus Paste{15%grams} and @Sugar{1%tsp}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat. Simmer, stirring occasionally, about ~{4-5%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Once the pasta is cooked, drain and add to the sauce.

Stir through three quarters of the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams}.

Add a splash of water to loosen if needed. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Serve in #bowls{} with the remaining cheese on top.

Enjoy!